The Saints and people of God have met with the same Treatment<lb/>
in all Ages. This has been their Lot and Portion, when<lb/>
they have lived amongst wicked loose People. And we generally<lb/>
find that they took great Satisfaction in it. Our blessed Saviour<lb/>
was used thus himself. How was he reviled, scorned, <normalised orig="reproach't" auto="true">reproached</normalised>,<lb/>
falsely accused, Spit upon, <normalised orig="Buffetted" auto="true">Buffeted</normalised>, <normalised orig="Whipt" auto="true">Whipped</normalised>, and at<lb/>
last disgracefully Crucified, by a degenerate inhumane People?<lb/>
You see the greatest and most absolute Innocence is not safe,<lb/>
from the Malicious rage, and violence of ungodly men. The<lb/>
Apostles presently after, were served in the same manner. And<lb/>
when they were Scourged, to render them a <normalised orig="publick" auto="true">public</normalised> scorn and<lb/>
reproach they went away <normalised orig="rejoycing" auto="true">rejoicing</normalised>, that they were counted<lb/>
worthy to be thus used for Christ. It is one part of the Vocation<lb/>
