of acquaintance with men of Power and Repute, who are Enemies<lb/>
to Protestants as such, may <normalised orig="ingage" auto="true">engage</normalised> you in those Practices,<lb/>
which both your deceitful Hearts and the better hopes of others,<lb/>
made you believe you should for ever detest.<lb/>
Satan very seldom Attempts to draw any man to direct Persecution<lb/>
at first; He only leads them at first to the out-skirts, and<lb/>
Fleshes them by degrees. But when he has once brought men to<lb/>
take Pleasure in seeing others suffer, tho not for real Religion, the<lb/>
